# {{ source_root }}/integrations/ — external-system clients

Thin, independently-removable clients for external systems. Shared knobs live
in `settings.py` (pydantic-settings, reads `.env`). Each module was selected
at scaffold time (`optional_features` / `external_systems`); add more later
without hand-rolling auth/retry patterns — copy the shape of an existing one.

{% if include_n8n_webhook -%}
- `n8n_webhook.py` — HMAC-verified inbound webhook receiver
  (`POST /webhooks/n8n`), auto-mounted on every present agent's FastAPI app.
{% endif -%}
{% if include_calendar_integration -%}
- `google_calendar.py` — Google Calendar client (pre-obtained OAuth2 refresh
  token).
{% endif -%}
{% if include_composio -%}
- `composio.py` — third-party app actions (Gmail/Slack/GitHub, hundreds more)
  via Composio's unified tool API.
{% endif -%}
{% if include_web_research -%}
- `web_research.py` — autonomous web research + reports via GPT-Researcher
  (needs Python ≤ 3.13 and its own API keys).
{% endif -%}
{% if include_meeting_intelligence -%}
- `meeting_intelligence.py` (+ `clients/`) — meeting transcript → structured
  action items/decisions via one LLM call.
{% endif -%}
{% if include_marketing_integrations -%}
- `eventbrite.py` / `linkedin.py` / `canva.py` — httpx clients for publishing
  events, posting updates, generating assets.
{% endif %}
Convention: integrations hold I/O + auth only — business logic belongs to the
agent or pipeline that calls them.
